;[[

; Tronex
; Dynamic World Items

; In Anomaly 1.5, the Zone will be filled with items based on recorded positions and suitable types to spawn
; Items spawned by all.spawn will be completely replaced as well
; The total number of dynamic world items is determined by "random_items" factor, it can be found under Progression Difficulty settings
; When player takes one these items, another will be spawned in a different place to keep the cycle on going
; There are 6 item categories, each consist of a group of possible items to spawn
; Down below, you can see how each level has a set of items names and their type / position, you can record positions and add them here if you want to see items appear there

;]]

;--================================================================================================================

[settings]
enabled = true	;-- true = Enable the feature

;-- Multiuse items in this list that are spawned dynamically will have possible uses defined here (min uses - max uses)
